The paper deals with the quantification of computational security, which is a core topic in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the analysis of probabilities and large deviation principles, which are common in information theory (cs.IT) and probability theory (cs.PR). The problem of identifying U strings selected by V users involves the manipulation and analysis of lists, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the asymptotic behavior of the number of guesses required, which is a topic in statistical inference (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
